♫ <i>The sun will rise and fall</i> ♫

102
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,800
♫ <i>It's just another day</i> ♫

103
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:52,000
This color isn't bright enough.

104
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
It's too simple.

105
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,300
Well, let's emboss it in silver.

106
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:57,400
The quality will be better.

107
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,800
What about hollowing it out?

108
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,700
Let's hollow out the packaging sash.

109
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:01,900
We'll keep the box simple.

110
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,000
I'll make a sample and show you.

111
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,400
Okay.

112
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,000
Hello, Brother?

113
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,500
What is it?

114
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,900
Okay, calm down. I'll be right there.

115
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,000
What's wrong?

116
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,000
It's nothing. You guys carry on.

117
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,800
<i>Give us money!</i>

118
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,400
Wait! Listen to me!

119
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:38,300
Calm down! You'll be paid eventually.

120
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:41,600
Won't we be wasting our efforts if we demolish this homestay?

121
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,200
The project was suddenly shut down,

122
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,400
and two months of our wages have been delayed.

123
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,000
Our boss has gone missing.

124
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,000
What are we supposed to do?

125
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Your boss called me. He's raising funds.

126
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,600
Fine, ask him to pay us.

127
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,600
- Right?
- Yes.

128
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,000
- Pay us!
- We need to keep ourselves fed!

129
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Isn't the village committee going to intervene?

130
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,300
You've gone to the village committee, so you should understand.

131
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:01,200
The secretary and the director are out for a meeting today.

132
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,500
We aren't neglecting you.

133
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,000
Enough with the excuses! Pay up!

134
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Everyone should pay their debts!

135
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,300
<i>Pay up!</i>

136
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Here! Over here!

137
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,800
Thanks!

138
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,800
<i>Pay up!</i>

139
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,200
Enough with your crap!

140
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,000
Old Xie! Old Xie!

141
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,300
Everyone, be quiet.

142
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,000
A'Yao is here. Let's hear what he has to say.

143
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,800
Why have you surrounded Xiao Huang?

144
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,600
Don't yell at a girl.

145
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,000
Let's settle the problem first.

146
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,300
Have a smoke, Brother.

147
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,200
Come on, take a cigarette.

148
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:47,000
Brother, I dropped everything at hand and rushed over to your call.

149
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,200
Let's focus on solving the problem.

150
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,500
Don't be angry, all right?

151
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,700
A'Yao, the boss has fled,

152
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:54,800
but he didn't pay our wages.

153
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:59,400
Yes, I promise to resolve the issue with your wages.

154
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,100
The boss has invested millions in this homestay.

155
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,700
The stuff here is worth hundreds of thousands.

156
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:05,500
A monk may run, but the temple remains. He has to return, right?

157
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,600
Yeah, compare the price of all these to your wages.

158
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,000
He wouldn't ditch everything here and flee.

159
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,400
Well, pay our wages!

160
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,200
Yes, pay us!

161
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,000
Pay up! Give us the money!

162
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,600
Enough. Hold on.

163
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:23,500
- A'Yao, you recruited us for this homestay.
- Yes.

164
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,000
Huang Xinxin is the guarantor.

165
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,800
You can't stay out of this.

166
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,700
In fact, we would've quit once wages weren't paid for a month.

167
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,600
But the boss treated us pretty well.

168
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,700
We can understand his difficulties.

169
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:39,400
So, we kept working even thought our wages were delayed.

170
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,700
He may be raising funds now,

171
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:45,200
but how long more do we have to wait?

172
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,300
Should we take on other jobs or not?

173
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:49,200
Do we have to keep on waiting?

174
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,300
No one is giving us answers.

175
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,000
Yes, you're right.

176
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:57,400
The homestay near the airport offered a higher price than this.

177
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:00,600
You said this place was nearer to our home,

178
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,800
and we can go home if we chose this project.

179
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:07,500
This also benefits our village's future development.

180
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,000
We agreed with you,

181
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,800
but the boss has gone missing.

182
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,200
We don't even get paid.

183
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,700
What should we do?

184
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:18,300
Brother, don't worry.

185
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:21,400
Xiao Huang and I will find a solution right away.

186
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,200
I'll look for you tonight and resolve this, all right?

187
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:29,600
I understand your frustration and worries.

188
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,800
You've done nothing wrong either,

189
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:34,400
but we can't solve any problems by standing here. Okay?

190
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,800
We'll find a solution right away and get you paid.

191
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:37,800
Are you okay with this?

192
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:40,000
Brother A'Yao is a bigwig,

193
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,000
so he's great at speaking up for bosses.

194
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,600
He's trying to coax us and stop us from causing trouble!

195
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,000
Everyone's just trying to work for a living.

196
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:51,200
Why do you make it sound like we're troublemakers, A'Quan?

197
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:54,900
Even television shows about the government, journalists,

198
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:58,300
or lawyers helping with wage issues take time.

199
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,400
Well, pay us! Darned brat!

200
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,200
Uncle!

201
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:05,000
Does A'Yao or the committee owe you money? Stupid boy!

202
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,700
Uncle, don't kick him.

203
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:09,300
He's frustrated because he's not getting paid for his work.

204
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,400
It's understandable.

205
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:13,120
Yeah. I'd be angry if I were in his shoes.

206
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,100
Don't stand around. You can go.

207
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:18,200
Why are you lingering here? It's such a hot day.

208
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,600
Your wages for today will be paid, too. All right?

209
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,500
Wait for news from us. Okay? All right?

210
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:23,600
Let's go home.

211
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,200
Guys, move it.

212
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,200
Wait for news at home.

213
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,200
Off you go! Move it!

214
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,200
Have a cigarette.

215
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,200
Come on. Get moving.

216
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,200
Wait for news at home.

217
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:38,200
Brother, have a smoke.

218
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:44,100
A'Yao, I trust you.

219
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:59,200
Take it easy!

220
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,400
My luck sure is amazing.

221
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,600
The secretary and village director just happen to be out.

222
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:12,500
I called the director, and he told me to take a look.

223
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,400
Once I arrived, they refused to listen to me.

224
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,800
I'm just one person.

225
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,500
How can I win in an argument against 20 others?

226
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:21,100
My throat, tongue, and lips are parched.

227
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,600
What's up with the homestay's owner?

228
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,600
Did he really go bankrupt?

229
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,200
I called him.

230
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:30,600
He said he's raising funds.

231
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,600
He spent so much money on this place.

232
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,200
Even if he really went bankrupt,

233
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:39,400
shouldn't he hurry back and sell this place?

234
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:42,400
This place isn't easy to sell.

235
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:48,400
If Shaohua Bookstore has a store here, it would be an easy deal.

236
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:53,600
When is your senior who's a photographer coming over?

237
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,700
She said she'll come over once she's done with her short film.

238
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:57,900
Okay.

239
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,200
Where's your Xu Hongdou?

240
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,200
Having fun somewhere.

241
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:05,600
Hey, she isn't mine.

242
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,400
Don't you know that you're getting married?

243
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,200
I don't know.

244
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,700
Xiao Qin.

245
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,000
What's wrong?

246
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,600
Did your dad scold you again?

247
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,500
<i>WeChat scan.</i>

248
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,000
Brother A'Yao,

249
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,800
you told me on WeChat that your marriage is a rumor.

250
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,200
Is that true?

251
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,200
Yes, it is.

252
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,300
Call me Uncle A'Yao.

253
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,300
Well, can you marry me?

254
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:51,000
Of course not.

255
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,200
Why not?

256
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:56,200
You're disdainful of me for my lack of education and skills, right?

257
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,800
Xiao Qin,

258
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:01,200
when I was in junior high, you were a little girl.

259
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,400
I even carried you when you were a baby.

260
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:05,200
When I started working, I sent you gift money every year when I came back.

261
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,400
Do you remember this?

262
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,800
Some men like younger girls.

263
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:12,200
Some celebrities are 12 years older than their wives.

264
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,400
Isn't that right, Xinxin?

